4 HR____ COMMENDING ALABAMIANS CHRIS RICHARDS AND TANNER
5 TESSMANN FOR REPRESENTING THE UNITED STATES IN THE WORLD
6 CUP.
7
8 WHEREAS, Chris Richards and Tanner Tessmann are two
9 soccer athletes from Alabama who are positioned to be on the
10 U.S. roster for this summer's World Cup; and
11 WHEREAS, a native of Hoover, Chris Richards is
12 projected to be the first team captain from Alabama; he has
13 been named the 2025 United States Soccer Male Player of the
14 Year and now plays for South London team Crystal Palace; and
15 WHEREAS, in just a few short years, Chris Richards
16 has managed to play for teams in three different countries;
17 the 26-year-old got his start playing for clubs in Dallas
18 and Houston, Texas; after that, he went to Munich and
19 Sinsheim, Germany; his first position at his current team,
20 Crystal Palace, was as a defensive midfielder rather than
21 his preferred center back role; however, these experiences
22 perfectly prepared him to be the most important defender for
23 the U.S., and on the biggest sports stage in the world; and
24 WHEREAS, Chris Richards has been instrumental in the
25 construction of a new soccer field in front of the historic
26 Powell Avenue steam plant in Birmingham's Railroad Park and
27 UAB Hospital area; he partnered with Fédération
28 Internationale de Football Association (FIFA), soccer's
Page 1

Internationale de Football Association (FIFA), soccer's
HR342 INTRODUCED
29 global governing body, to bring the small-sided field to
30 downtown Birmingham as part of FIFA's "soccer forward"
31 campaign; and
32 WHEREAS, also a native of Hoover, Tanner Tessmann was
33 captain of the 2024 U.S. Olympic soccer team in Paris; he
34 was also named the 2024 Young Male Player of the Year by the
35 United States Soccer Federation; and
36 WHEREAS, Tanner Tessmann, a 24-year-old defensive
37 midfielder, is both a talented soccer player and football
38 kicker; he had planned to play both sports at Clemson
39 University but instead signed a contract with FC Dallas; his
40 soccer path then took him to the Italian club Venezia for
41 three years before his current role with Olympique Lyonnais
42 in France; and
43 WHEREAS, now Tanner Tessmann has played for two of
44 Europe's top five leagues, Italy's Serie A in 2021-22 before
45 relegation and France's Ligue 1 the past two seasons, while
46 simultaneously climbing the U.S. ladder; since playing every
47 minute of four Olympic matches in France, he has integrated
48 into the senior squad of the United States Men's National
49 Soccer Team; last fall, he started twice and came off the
50 bench twice, scoring in the 5-1 disastrous defeat of Uruguay
51 in Tampa; with World Cup veteran Tyler Adams recovering from
52 a knee injury, Tanner Tessmann's role could expand this
53 spring; and
54 WHEREAS, Alabama can be proud of its native sons,
55 Chris Richards and Tanner Tessmann; they are tenacious
56 players who will help advance Team USA further in the
Page 2

players who will help advance Team USA further in the
HR342 INTRODUCED
57 knockout round than any American team has ever advanced; now
58 therefore,
59 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE
60 LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA, That we wish to commemorate this
61 historic event and heartily commend Chris Richards and
62 Tanner Tessmann for their significance as role models with
63 the talent and ability to represent Alabama on an
64 international level.
